# Features

## Missing/Incomplete Features

☐ Article bookmarking / read-later queue — Star rating exists (1-5) but there's no dedicated "save for later" or bookmarks list. A simple boolean isBookmarked with a Bookmarks sidebar section would be high-value.
☐ Export / share — No way to share article links externally (system share sheet, copy link, etc.). macOS has a native Share button that integrates with Safari, Notes, etc.
☐ Keyboard navigation — No apparent keyboard shortcuts for navigating between articles (J/K like classic RSS readers), marking read (M), starring (S), or opening detail (Enter/Space). These are expected by power users.
✔ Fetch on launch / auto-refresh — There's no background periodic refresh. The app only fetches when the user manually hits Refresh or adds a source. A configurable auto-refresh interval (e.g., every 15/30/60 min) would keep the feed current. @done(Tue. 04/14/2026 - 11:16:45 PM)
☐ Unread count badges — SidebarView shows unread count for "All Articles" but it's unclear if per-source unread counts appear. Even a small badge per source helps navigation.
☐ Mark all read — No bulk "mark all as read" action. Users accumulate hundreds of articles fast.
✔ OPML import/export — RSS managers conventionally support OPML for migrating feed lists. Without it, switching to/from Reeder, NetNewsWire, etc. is painful. @done(Mon. 04/14/2026 - 11:34:00 PM)
✔ Article text size / font controls — ArticleWebContentView hardcodes 17px Georgia. A font-size slider in Settings (or toolbar) would help readability. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 02:00:00 PM)
✘ AI batch processing — Ollama rewrites happen one article at a time, triggered manually. A "rewrite all visible headlines" batch option would make the AI feature much more useful. @cancelled(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 11:35:03 AM)
✘ Image gallery / full-screen image — No way to zoom/expand thumbnail images in article detail. @cancelled(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 11:34:53 AM)

## Usability

✘ Article detail is a sheet, not a split panel — On a large macOS display, a NavigationSplitView with a third detail column would be far more natural than a full-screen modal sheet. The current sheet covers the entire grid and kills browsing momentum. @cancelled(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 11:04:14 AM)
✘ Read articles don't persist scroll position — When the user returns from article detail, the grid likely resets. Scroll position should be preserved across detail open/close. @cancelled(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 11:04:19 AM)
✘ No "next article" / "previous article" navigation in detail — Users have to close the sheet and reopen the next card. An arrow button (or swipe gesture) to step through articles sequentially is a basic reader feature. @cancelled(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 11:04:20 AM)
☐ Tag filter is all-or-nothing — Tags appear to be AND or OR but it's not communicated. Clarifying the filter logic (or letting users toggle it) prevents confusion.
☐ Source error is in context menu only — The warning icon on a source with lastError only reveals the error via right-click. Hovering to show a tooltip with the error text would be much more discoverable.
☐ No confirmation on "Hide article" — The hide button appears on hover with no undo. A brief "Undo" toast/notification would prevent accidental hides.
☐ Search scope is unclear — Does search cover title only? Author? Summary? Content? There's no indication, and users will be confused by non-obvious results.
☐ Settings are in a separate window — The Ollama + weather settings are in a standard Settings scene, but some of these (especially Ollama model selection ad test connection) feel like they belong in the Source Manager or a quick-access popover.
☐ No loading indicator at the per-source level — During refresh, you can't tell which sources are currently fetching vs. done. A subtle spinner next to each source in the sidebar would help.

## Performance

✔ ReadabilityService uses WKWebView on every detail open — Even for cached articles, loadContent() in ArticleDetailViewModel still invokes the Readability pipeline if readableContent is nil. Cached content should short-circuit immediately without touching WKWebView at all. @done(Mon. 04/14/2026 - 11:52:00 PM)
✔ Image loading has no explicit cache policy — AsyncImage uses the default URL cache. For a news app where the same thumbnail may appear on the grid card and in the detail view, using URLCache with a defined size limit or a proper image cache (e.g., NSCache) would reduce redundant network hits. @done(Mon. 04/14/2026 - 11:52:00 PM)
✔ Tag filtering runs a full DB query on every keypress in search — applySearch in ArticlesViewModel triggers initialLoad(). A debounce (e.g., 300ms) on searchText changes would reduce needless DB hits. @done(Mon. 04/14/2026 - 11:52:00 PM)
✔ Parallel feed refresh with no concurrency cap — FeedRefreshService uses TaskGroup to fetch all enabled sources simultaneously. With 30+ sources enabled, this spawns 30+ concurrent network requests. A bounded semaphore or withTaskGroup with a max parallelism of ~5-8 would be more resource-friendly. @done(Mon. 04/14/2026 - 11:52:00 PM)
✔ rewriteWithAI is called on a per-article basis with no queue — If a user triggers multiple AI rewrites in rapid succession, they go to Ollama serially and each blocks on a response. An AsyncStream-based queue with cancellation support would be cleaner. @done(Mon. 04/14/2026 - 11:52:00 PM)
✔ Pagination prefetch threshold of 10 items — With 40-item pages, triggering prefetch at 10 items remaining is probably fine, but the next page load is synchronous-feeling. Pre-fetching at 15-20 items with smooth skeleton insertion would eliminate visible load pauses. @done(Mon. 04/14/2026 - 11:52:00 PM)

## UI Usability

✔ Article grid uses a single adaptive column (280–400pt) — On a large monitor (27–32"), this results in 3-4 very wide cards. A true multi-column newspaper layout (e.g., 2–3 fixed columns like a broadsheet) would be far more appropriate for the "newspaper" aesthetic. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:14:00 AM)
✔ Tag chips have no maximum width enforcement — Long tag names can stretch the filter bar awkwardly. Truncating chip labels at ~12 chars with a tooltip would tighten the bar. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:14:00 AM)
✔ Star ratings on the card are too small for confident clicking — 5 star symbols at 14pt article card density are easy to mis-tap. Moving ratings to the detail view (where there's space) or making stars larger on hover would help. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:14:00 AM)
✔ Skeleton loading uses fixed 4 cards — If the user has 1-2 articles visible before paginating, 4 skeleton cards will overshoot the visible area. Calculating the visible row count and matching the skeleton count would look cleaner. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:14:00 AM)
✔ Source color assignment via hash is invisible to the user — Users can't customize source colors. A color picker per source in Source Manager would let them create their own visual taxonomy. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:14:00 AM)
✔ Empty state messaging could be more specific — When articles are empty due to a search that returns nothing vs. all sources being disabled vs. no articles fetched yet, the same empty state likely appears. Contextual empty states improve clarity. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:14:00 AM)
✔ No dark mode thumbnail handling — Dark mode likely inverts some article thumbnails oddly depending on image content. A subtle darkening overlay on thumbnails in dark mode would look more consistent. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 11:03:40 AM)
✘ Hover-only hide button is discoverable only by accident — Consider making it always-visible as a faint X, or accessible via right-click context menu. @cancelled(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 11:03:53 AM)


Highest impact (core reader experience):

☐ Keyboard navigation is the biggest gap for a desktop news app. Power users expect J/K to move between articles, Enter to open, M to mark read, O to open in browser. Without it the app feels like it hasn't committed to being a Mac app.

✔ "Mark all read" — articles accumulate fast. Without a bulk action the read-status feature becomes useless noise after a few days. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 01:03:36 PM)

☐ Article bookmarking — the star ratings exist but a simple dedicated Bookmarks queue (isBookmarked + sidebar section) is more intuitive than a rating for "save this." Ratings and bookmarks serve different purposes.

Architecture gaps not yet in the TODO:

✔ Article aging / database cleanup — there's no mechanism to prune old articles. The DB will grow unbounded over time. A configurable retention window (e.g., keep last 30/60/90 days, always keep unread and bookmarked) would prevent this. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:39:05 PM)

✔ Full-text search — ArticleRepository.fetch() searches title, author, and summary only. Readable content is cached in readableContent but isn't searched. FTS5 (SQLite full-text search, which GRDB supports natively) would make search dramatically more useful. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:39:08 PM)

✔ ReadabilityService has a concurrency hazard — it's a singleton with a single pendingContinuation. If two articles are opened quickly (or the same article opened twice), the second call overwrites pendingContinuation and the first caller's continuation is leaked/never resumed. It needs a queue or per-call WebView instances. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:39:10 PM)

✔ Feed discovery — when a user adds a website URL (not a feed URL), the app currently marks it as a "website" type but doesn't attempt RSS autodiscovery (parsing <link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml"> from the homepage). NetNewsWire and Reeder both do this; it dramatically lowers the friction of adding sources. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:39:12 PM)

Polish that would matter for going public:

✔ Share sheet / Copy Link — there's no way to share an article. A toolbar button with NSSharingServicePicker or a right-click context menu with "Copy Link" is a one-liner and covers the most common action. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:49:05 PM)

✔ Search scope label — the search bar gives no indication what it searches. A small (title, author, summary) footer hint or a scope picker would eliminate confusion. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:49:03 PM)

✔ Per-source unread badges — you track unread per article but the sidebar source rows don't show counts. This is how users decide which source to read first. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:49:00 PM)

✔ Notification on new articles — a UNUserNotificationCenter post when a background refresh finds new articles (opt-in, with a count) is a standard expectation for any feed reader. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 12:48:59 PM)

Lower priority but worth noting:


☐ iCloud/CloudKit sync — UserDefaults settings and Keychain are local-only. If someone runs the app on two Macs there's no sync. Complex to add but worth planning the data model for.

✔ Ollama endpoint validation — currently accepts any URL; a user (or someone with local access) could point it at an arbitrary remote host. A simple localhost-only warning would be a sensible guardrail. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 02:00:00 PM)

✔ Font size controls — already in your TODO; easy win, big readability impact. @done(Wed. 04/15/2026 - 02:00:00 PM)

